-- Mexico Stocks: Chedraui, Wal-Mart de Mexico Gain; Mexichem Drops
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2011-12-21T22:05:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-21/mexico-stocks-chedraui-wal-mart-de-mexico-gain-mexichem-drops.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Mexico trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading.  The IPC  index (MEXBOL)  rose 1.1 percent to 36,628.06.  Mexican stocks rose, reversing earlier losses, as consumer
staples and retail companies benefited from holiday sales.  Grupo Comercial Chedraui SA (CHDRAUIB MM), the supermarket
chain based in Xalapa, Mexico, rose 1.7 percent to 34.28 pesos.
 Grupo Modelo SA (GMODELOC)  , Mexico’s largest beer maker,
advanced 2.3 percent to 88.82 pesos.  Wal-Mart de Mexico SAB (WALMEXV) 
, Latin America’s largest retailer, rose 1.5 percent
to 37.46 pesos.  Mexichem SAB (MEXCHEM*)  , Latin America’s biggest maker
of plastic pipes, declined 0.2 percent to 45.15 pesos. The
company said in an e-mailed statement that it’s still seeking to
acquire Wavin NV.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in  Mexico  City at 
 jlevin20@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
